New Zealand Rugby World Cup Organizers Say 1 Million Tickets Sold So Far

-- B y   D a n   B a y n e s
-- 
2011-07-06T05:13:20Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-06/n-z-rugby-world-cup-organizers-say-1-million-tickets-sold-for-tournament.html
Rugby World Cup organizers said
ticket sales for this year’s tournament in  New Zealand  reached
NZ$220 million ($182 million), or about 82 percent of their
final revenue target.  One million tickets have been sold for the Sept. 9-Oct. 23
tournament after the final phase of sales began July 4, Rugby
New Zealand 2011 Ltd. said today in an e-mailed statement.  “This is about where we expected to be with little over
two months until the tournament kicks off,” RNZ 2011 Ltd. Chief
Executive Officer Martin Snedden said in the statement.  Organizers forecast total sales revenue of NZ$268 million
based on selling 1.35 million tickets for the 48 matches.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dan Baynes at 
 dbaynes@bloomberg.net  